[{"question":"I mean, there must have been a point where you thought you were all going to die, wasn\u0027t there?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":66,"aSentId":67},{"question":"Kyung, what\u0027s the latest from where you are?","answer":"From where we are, we\u0027re starting to continue to see more and more damage, Piers, as we get closer and closer.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":82,"aSentId":83},{"question":"Do you have any sense from what you\u0027re seeing, from what you\u0027re hearing about any kind of death toll?","answer":"It\u0027s really hard to imagine.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":95,"aSentId":96},{"question":"Can you describe to me what is actually going on?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":125,"aSentId":126},{"question":"Could you please start by telling me what your understanding of the scale of this disaster is in terms of people who\u0027ve been wounded, possibly killed?","answer":"Thank you very much, Mr. Morgan, for giving me this opportunity.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":135,"aSentId":136},{"question":"I mean are you fearing here -- that you may be seeing a toll much, much higher?","answer":"As what I said is the figure that we have identified up to now.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":154,"aSentId":155},{"question":"Can you tell me what the latest is in relation to those plants?","answer":"Yes, we are talking about the Fukushima nuclear power plant, and there are two sites.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":165,"aSentId":166},{"question":"I mean, is it possible we could see a meltdown of one of these plants?","answer":"I am sorry, I\u0027m not in a position to speculate on that.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":175,"aSentId":176},{"question":"Ken, can I start with you and just ask you what you think is going on from an expert point of view here?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s not the answer you want to hear, but I would say that statistical analysis would have a hard time finding a pattern here.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":204,"aSentId":205},{"question":"Is this actually how it sounds?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":210,"aSentId":211},{"question":"What do you think is happening here?","answer":"Well, I think Ken has a good point that if you looked at the geological history of this area, there\u0027s been repeated tsunamis generated in the Sendai area.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":219,"aSentId":220},{"question":"Is this complete nonsense, or is there any kind of credence to that theory?","answer":"It\u0027s complete nonsense, but I don\u0027t like saying it\u0027s nonsense without defending why it is so.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":234,"aSentId":235},{"question":"Is this one of the inevitable repercussions of an earthquake that size?","answer":"Well, aftershocks do follow some general patterns and can be statistically analyzed.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":260,"aSentId":261},{"question":"What possible comfort can you offer them?","answer":"ERKUS: Well, there\u0027s several things.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":296,"aSentId":297},{"question":"Given we\u0027ve experienced this before there, what do you think is the most sensible and immediate thing that should be done to help the people in Japan?","answer":"I think people should be texting to the Red Cross.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":334,"aSentId":335},{"question":"Matthew, if I may start with you, what is your understanding of the latest situation at the Fukushima plant?","answer":"They -- when you shut down a nuclear plant, you\u0027re continuing to produce heat.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":371,"aSentId":372},{"question":"What is the hour-by-hour time scale that we could be looking at before there\u0027s some sort of inevitable meltdown?","answer":"At this point, a meltdown is not inevitable.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":382,"aSentId":383},{"question":"How serious do you think this one is in Japan?","answer":"Well, actually there haven\u0027t been very many situations of this degree of seriousness.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":401,"aSentId":402},{"question":"And what does it mean for nuclear plants in America, for example, if a similar thing was to happen here?","answer":"There\u0027s the beginning of renaissance in nuclear construction all over Asia and, to some extent, in the United States.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":413,"aSentId":414},{"question":"And if so, are we prepared to deal with it?","answer":"First of all, Piers, our hearts and prayers are with the people of Japan, and the -- the Japanese American community that lives here in Los Angeles, the largest in the United States.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":436,"aSentId":437},{"question":"How fast can these tsunamis strike, can these quakes strike?","answer":"Well, I\u0027m not an expert on that, but I can tell you the following: I got in real-time on my Blackberry.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":445,"aSentId":446},{"question":"Is that just crass stupidity, in your view?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":455,"aSentId":456},{"question":"Have you in your lifetime seen anything quite like what we witnessed in Japan in the last 24 hours?","answer":"No, definitely not.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":473,"aSentId":474},{"question":"What is the ring of fire and what does it mean now going forward?","answer":"Incredibly active zone, Piers.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":483,"aSentId":484},{"question":"Is it now completely unpredictable?","answer":"Piers, if I could forecast the weather for the rest of the year, I would do it right now, go home and call it a day.","docId":"110311pmt","qSentId":518,"aSentId":519}]